<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1794,1992]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
Remarks. This new species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran, 2006" authorityName="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran" authorityYear="2006" box="[695,1124,1829,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Aclista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leana">
<emphasis box="[695,783,1829,1853]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">A. leana</emphasis>
Rajmohana &amp; Narendran, 2006
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by following characteristics: A3 6.00× as long as wide, and 0.79× scape length (4.00× and 0.60× respectively in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Aclista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">A. leana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); A15 0.50× A3 length (
<quantity box="[454,529,1898,1922]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6764" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" unit="in" value="0.66">0.66 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran" authorityYear="2006" box="[534,622,1898,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Aclista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leana">
<emphasis box="[534,622,1898,1922]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">A. leana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pronotal collar indistinct in dorsal view (distinct in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran" authorityYear="2006" box="[1186,1274,1898,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Aclista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leana">
<emphasis box="[1186,1274,1898,1922]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">A. leana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); fore wing with radial cell 3.38× as long as marginal vein (2.00× in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran" authorityYear="2006" box="[682,770,1933,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Aclista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leana">
<emphasis box="[682,770,1933,1957]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">A. leana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and petiole 1.33× as long as middle width (more than 2.00× in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rajmohana &amp; Narendran" authorityYear="2006" box="[136,225,1967,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Aclista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leana">
<emphasis box="[136,225,1967,1991]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">A. leana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
